## 1. File System Integration

### Purpose
Locate and read `.b` → `.d` → `target.rp` folder hierarchies for scanning and parsing.

### Access modes
- **Local path:** Standard OS file path (e.g. `C:\Data\Run001.b` on Windows, `/data/Run001.b` on Linux/Mac)
- **Network path:** UNC paths (e.g. `\\server\share\Run001.b`) and mapped drive letters (e.g. `Z:\Run001.b`)

### Operations
- List contents of a directory
- Check for existence of a folder or file
- Open and read file contents from `target.rp`

### Constraints
- Read-only — the app never writes to the source file system
- Must handle path-not-found gracefully (prompt user to verify path)
- Must handle permission-denied gracefully (prompt user to check access)
- Network path timeout behavior must be handled — do not hang indefinitely on unreachable paths

### Failure handling
| Failure | Expected behavior |
|---|---|
| `.b` path does not exist | Display error before scan begins; no scan starts |
| `.b` path is not accessible (permission denied) | Display error before scan begins; no scan starts |
| Network path becomes unavailable mid-scan | Flag affected `.d` folders as errored; continue with accessible folders; report in summary |
| `.d` folder exists but `target.rp` is missing | Flag sample as `missing_target_rp`; continue scan |
| `target.rp` file exists but cannot be read | Flag sample as `parse_error`; continue scan |

