## 3. Excel Export (.xlsx)

### Purpose
Generate formatted Excel files containing compound data filtered by user-selected batches (or full DB).

### Library
- `openpyxl` (preferred) or equivalent
- No dependency on Microsoft Excel being installed

### Output format
- File extension: `.xlsx`
- Columns: Batch name, Sample folder name, Compound number, Compound name, U-Del comment, Is U-Del (boolean)
- Summary row or sheet: U-Del detection count per compound per batch (derived at export time)
- Formatting: Column headers bolded, column widths auto-sized to content, no conditional color formatting required in v1

### Export scope
- User selects one or more batches from a checklist, OR selects "Full DB Export"
- Only the latest `ScanVersion` for each selected batch is included in the export (not historical versions)
- User sees version number and scan date for each batch at selection time

### Failure handling
| Failure | Expected behavior |
|---|---|
| No batches selected | Export button disabled or grayed until selection is made |
| Write permission error on output path | Display error with file path; allow user to choose different output location |
| openpyxl not installed | App startup check; clear error message with install instructions |

