## 5. No external integrations in v1

The following are explicitly out of scope:
- LIMS systems
- Cloud storage (S3, SharePoint, OneDrive, etc.)
- Email or notification services
- Authentication providers (LDAP, Active Directory, SSO)
- Any external HTTP API

---

## Notes for the agent
- Trinity is a library, not a service. Do not add HTTP client calls to interact with it.
- All file system access is read-only. Never write to the source `.b` / `.d` folder hierarchy.
- Export generation must query Trinity — do not re-scan the file system at export time.
- SQLite WAL mode should be enabled at DB initialization for better concurrent access behavior.
- Wrap all Trinity commit operations in transactions. Never allow partial writes.